{
  "doc_id": "46942",
  "text": "High passage, avirulent B. burgdorferi strain B31A [CITATION_1] , and low passage virulent strain B31A3 [CITATION_2] , were grown at 33uC (except as noted) in the presence of 3% carbon dioxide in BSKII growth medium [CITATION_3] . Cell counts were determined using flow cytometry as previously described [CITATION_4] . These strains were originally obtained from P. Rosa, Rocky Mountain Laboratories, MT. The virulent, low passage strain B31MI [CITATION_5] was grown in vitro at 23uC, 37uC, and in in vivo in dialysis membrane chambers (DMCs) in Sprague-Dawley rats [CITATION_6] . For in vivo growth, sterilized dialysis membranes with a molecular weight cut-off of 8000 Da were filled with , 9 ml BSKII medium containing late logarithmic phase B. burgdorferi strain B31MI diluted to a starting density of 3000 spirochetes/ml. DMCs were aseptically implanted into the peritoneal cavities of female Sprague Dawley rats, and then harvested 14 days post-implantation as previously described [CITATION_7] . B. burgdorferi recombinant FlgE (rFlgE) was expressed in E. coli BL21 cells grown at 37uC in Luria-Bertani broth containing 100 mg/ml ampicillin and purified as previously described [CITATION_8] .",
